		<h3>2020 Coronavirus School Closing<br>
</h3>
		
		
		
		
		
			<p class="summary">April 2, 2020 Update from Mr. Remaly</p>
		
		
		
			<span class="text rteSpan">Bulldog Parents,<br><br>The Governor announced today that schools will remain closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. If you have been following the news, this should not come as a big surprise but it is definitely the right thing to do.<br><br>Our new normal of e learning will continue under the current format for the remainder of the year. Clinton Central will also continue to use the waiver days allowed and in the next couple of days, I will be sending out a calendar for the remainder of the year. I know there will be questions about graduation, credits, being promoted to the next grade, etc… Once the administrators and I know all of the specifics, we will communicate them to you.<br><br>I do want you to know that the staff is working incredibly hard on the e learning lessons. Each of our schools are holding regular ZOOM meetings with the teachers where they are discussing the areas of concern, the positives, and sharing a ton of ideas.  I was able to “attend” 6 of the sessions today and I was very impressed!<br><br>Parents, all of us at Clinton Central understand that e learning is different and has created new challenges for you. In no way do we expect for you to be the teacher and that is why I am asking you to encourage your student to stay engaged with their assignments and contact the teachers as needed. You can help by checking to make sure your child has completed their work. Again, if you or your child have questions, do not hesitate to contact the teacher.<br><br>As mentioned previously, you will be receiving specific information very soon. I greatly appreciate your continued support and remember that we are all in this together.<br><br>Al Remaly</span><br><div align="right">
		<br clear="both"><br>
</div>
		
		
		
	
		
		
		
		
		
